Article 13: Courts and Remedies

Section 1:
Wherein when this Constitution, or any contract entered into under it, is breached, a Voluntary Adherent shall have the right to seek remedy in any impartial court competent in contract law and which claims jurisdiction over the matter.

Section 2:
It is hereby established that the DAO holds the authority to adjudicate disputes between Voluntary Adherents, including claims arising from breaches of this Constitution or related agreements.

Section 3:
The DAO may delegate dispute resolution to an invested Voluntary Adherent or to a panel of Voluntary Adherents, provided such delegation is consistent with this Constitution.

Section 4: 
Wherein whenever Voluntary Adherents enter contractual agreements between each other, this Conatitution forms a binding part of that contract whether explicitly contemplated by the contract or not.
